    <h2>Whats included in Holy Grail?</h2>

    <div class="grid">

      <div class="mar_x_neg_1 clearfix">
        <div class="col col_6 col_lg_12 pad_x_1">

          <h4>Typography:</h4>

          <ul>
            <li>All typographic elements are fitted to a <a href="http://webdesign.tutsplus.com/articles/improving-layout-with-vertical-rhythm--webdesign-14070" target="_blank">vertical rhythm</a></li>
            <li>The <code>font-size</code>, <code>margin</code>, and <code>padding</code> of all content elements are proportionally set to a <a href="http://type-scale.com/" target="_blank">modular scale</a></li>
            <li>Optional responsive typography to get the most out of smaller viewports</li>
            <li>...And nothing else. We set a sane baseline and GTFO</li>
          </ul>

        </div>

        <div class="col col_6 col_lg_12 pad_x_1">

          <h4>Opt-in Responsive Layouts:</h4>

          <ul>
            <li><a href="{{ file.frontMatter.relative_nav_url }}layouts/two_left_2.html">Configurable fluid or fixed width content support with support for pixel and rem based units</a></li>
            <li>Optional <a href="{{ file.frontMatter.relative_nav_url }}features/sidebars_offcanvas.html">off-canvas fly-out sidebars</a></li>
            <li>1 content + <strong>1 or 2</strong> sidebars justified left <strong>or</strong> right</li>
            <li>1 content + 2 sidebars justified left <strong>and</strong> right</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid">

      <div class="mar_x_neg_1 clearfix">

        <div class="col col_6 col_lg_12 pad_x_1">

          <h4>Opt-in Modules:</h4>

          <p>As time progresses we will be developing additional common front-end modules. We've already got a great head-start:</p>

          <ul>
            <li><a href="{{ file.frontMatter.relative_nav_url }}features/forms.html">Forms &amp; Buttons</a></li>
